# .NET build output / intermediates — regenerated by `dotnet restore` +
# `dotnet build` + `dotnet pack`. NOT committed: the demo
# (deploy/demo/maf_dotnet) builds from source (`dotnet build`), the
# dotnet-build CI restores + builds + packs fresh and uploads the .nupkg as a
# downloadable artifact, the package is "build from repo" (not on NuGet), and
# `bp`-style local consumers restore from NuGet. Every dependency is a
# PackageReference / ProjectReference (NuGet-restored) — nothing here is
# vendored. Committed copies could only drift from source — the same
# stale-artifact bug fixed for the TS adapters (botpress / flowise / openclaw /
# core sdk all build-fresh too).
bin/
obj/
dist/
*.nupkg
*.snupkg

# Visual Studio / Rider per-user scratch.
*.user
.vs/
